{{distinguish|John Rudnicki}} {{Infobox comedian | name = Jon Rudnitsky | image = Jon Rudnitsky.jpg | image_size = 230px | caption = Rudnitsky performing in July 2016. | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|11|22}} | birth_place = [[Harrington Park, New Jersey]], U.S. | medium = Stand-up, film, television | active = 2011-present | website = {{URL|http://www.jonrudnitsky.com/}} }}
'''Jon Rudnitsky''' (born November 22, 1989)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc.com/saturday-night-live/blog/jon-rudnitsky-joins-snl-cast |title=Jon Rudnitsky Joins SNL Cast &#124; Blog |publisher=NBC |date= |accessdate=2015-09-19}}</ref> is an American actor and comedian who was a cast member on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' for the [[Saturday Night Live (season 41)|2015-2016]] season.
==Early life== Rudnitsky is a native of [[Harrington Park, New Jersey]].<ref name="cast">{{cite news |last=Zhu |first=Danielle |url= http://www.ew.com/article/2015/08/31/jon-rudnitsky-saturday-night-live-best-sketches |title=Meet Jon Rudnitsky, SNL's newest cast member |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=2015-08-31 |accessdate=}}</ref> His mother, Karen, is in charge of the gerontology center at Valley Hospital in Ridgewood.<ref>http://njjewishnews.com/article/27884/michael-orens-parents-recall-his-out-there-youth#.WwvBM0iFPcs</ref> He attended [[Northern Valley Regional High School at Old Tappan]].<ref>Sheridan, Angeline. [http://npascackvalley.macaronikid.com/article/1053981/heres-whats-buzzing-in-bergen-this-week "Here's What's Buzzing in Bergen This Week"], Macaroni Kid Northeast Bergen, September 3, 2015. Accessed September 8, 2015. "NBC recently announced the addition of 25 year old Jon Rudnitsky as a featured player on ''Saturday Night Live''. Rudnitsky, who grew up in Harrington Park, is a stand-up comedian who got his start at Northern Valley Old Tappan High School."</ref> He subsequently studied acting at the [[University of Southern California]]. His uncle (mother's brother) is [[Michael Oren]], the former Israeli ambassador to the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Mazel-Tov-MK-Michael-Oren-congratulates-nephew-on-joining-cast-of-SNL-415297 |title=MK Michael Oren congratulates nephew on joining cast of SNL - Israel News - Jerusalem Post |publisher=Jpost.com |date= |accessdate=2015-09-19}}</ref> Rudnitsky is [[Jewish]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Nate|last=Bloom|url=http://www.jweekly.com/2015/09/18/celebrtiey-jews0918/|title=celebrity jews |date=18 September 2015|work=J. The Jewish News of Northern California}}</ref>
==Career== Rudnitsky performed with [[the Groundlings]].<ref name="featured">{{cite news |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url= http://deadline.com/2015/08/saturday-night-jon-rudnitsky-new-featured-player-2015-1201510559/ |title=‘Saturday Night Live’ Adds Comedian Jon Rudnitsky To Cast As Featured Player |work=Deadline.com |date=2015-08-31 |accessdate=}}</ref> On August 31, 2015, it was announced that Rudnitsky would join the cast of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' as a featured player for the show's [[Saturday Night Live (season 41)|forty-first season]].<ref name="snl">{{cite news |last=Arkin |first=Daniel |url= http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/tv/jon-rudnitsky-stand-comic-joins-saturday-night-live-featured-player-n418826 |title=Jon Rudnitsky, Stand-Up Comic, Joins 'Saturday Night Live' as Featured Player |work=[[NBC News]] |date=2015-08-31 |accessdate=}}</ref> In the third episode of that season, Rudnitsky portrayed [[Anderson Cooper]] in a sketch, acting as moderator for a Democratic presidential debate, for which he was criticized by Cooper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/10/23/saturday-night-live-anderson-cooper-impression|title=Anderson Cooper offended by 'SNL' newcomer's impression|access-date=2016-07-02}}</ref> He has also done impressions of [[Wolf Blitzer]], [[John Mayer]], [[Martin Scorsese]], [[Tom Cruise]], and [[Vladimir Putin]] (in a dress rehearsal sketch on the episode hosted by [[Donald Trump]]), while also doing a Dirty Dancing sketch for Weekend Update, which was seen as one of his high points of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/140179-snl-newbie-jon-rudnitsky-finally-makes-his-mark-on-the-show-with-a-dirty-dancing-parody|title='SNL' Newbie Jon Rudnitsky Finally Makes His Mark On The Show With A 'Dirty Dancing' Parody|first=Marisa|last=LaScala|work=Bustle.com}}</ref> On August 9, 2016, Rudnitsky departed the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/08/saturday-night-live-jon-rudnitsky-featured-player-depart-1201800755/|title=‘Saturday Night Live’ Featured Player Jon Rudnitsky To Depart|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=9 August 2016|work=Deadline.com}}</ref>
In 2017, Rudnitsky starred alongside [[Reese Witherspoon]] in the romantic comedy film ''[[Home Again (2017 film)|Home Again]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jon-rudnitsky-joins-reese-witherspoon-home-again-943219|title='SNL' Alum Jon Rudnitsky Joins Reese Witherspoon in 'Home Again' (Exclusive)|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2016-11-21}}</ref> In 2018 Jon played Mike in the Netflix release ''[[Set It Up]]''.
He has been announced as starring alongside [[Jane Lynch]] and [[Genevieve Angelson]] in the NBC pilot ''Relatively Happy.''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/jane-lynch-nbc-pilot-relatively-happy-1202008986/|title=Jane Lynch Joins NBC Pilot ‘Relatively Happy’|last=Schwindt|first=Oriana|date=2017-03-14|work=Variety|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref>
